      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "In a feudal system, a few very wealthy families own nearly all the land. As a result, they have tremendous power, particularly in rural areas where most people work in agriculture. These families typically also hold most political posts.",
      "media" : [ {
        "zid" : 4032258,
        "xid" : "4032258.mp3",
        "type" : "audio",
        "file" : "4032258.mp3"
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Similarly, tribal affiliation is very important in the west of the country. Tribal leaders often have great political power and influence.",
      "media" : [ {
        "zid" : 4032259,
        "xid" : "4032259.mp3",
        "type" : "audio",
        "file" : "4032259.mp3"
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "A new urban elite is emerging that challenges both feudal and tribal leaders.",
